Title: NexGen Booking Vision
Subhead: How not to get lost in the project without any constraints except time.

2025
Role: Design lead
Team: Director of Product, 2 designers
Goal: Create a vision of the booking experience taht will make Boulevard standout

Problem:
Boulevards customer profile has changed. 
Starting with hair salons and barbershops. 
In the recent years we got a growing market share of Medspa and other 
businesses that require more sophisticated booking. 
They often have stronger brands with memberships and loyalty programs and 
have a larger marketing budgets to bring new customers. 
The booking experience built and optimized for our more traditional 
audience was not cutting it anymore.   

Gameplan:
1. Find out the limitations of current experience. What do customers complain about.
2. Rethink from the first principles. What are the core needs of our users.
3. Create an appealing vision that everu stakeholder can get behind.
4. Break it into self-contained projects and drive roadmap changes to make it happen. 




